= Builder API (Java) =

The builder API is the code-first path for composing stories with compile-time structure checks.

== Core Builders ==
* ''StoryBuilder''
* ''StoryNodeBuilder''
* ''StoryChoiceBuilder''
* ''StoryActionBuilder''
* ''StoryTriggerBuilder''

== Example ==
<syntaxhighlight lang="java">
Story story = new StoryBuilder()
    .setId("epic_quest")
    .setName("The Epic Quest")
    .setStartNode("intro")
    .addNode(new StoryNodeBuilder()
        .setId("intro")
        .addText("Welcome, adventurer!")
        .addChoice(new StoryChoiceBuilder()
            .setText("I accept!")
            .setNext("quest_start")
            .addAction(StoryActionBuilder.giveItem("quest_token", 1).build())
            .build())
        .build())
    .build();
</syntaxhighlight>

== Why Use Builders ==
* Type-safe construction of stories in Java.
* Reusable factory helpers for actions and triggers.
* Better refactoring support in IDEs.
* Easy integration into custom generation pipelines.

== Typical Workflow ==
# Build story definitions with builders.
# Validate generated story objects.
# Export/package JSON assets for runtime loading.

== Practical Notes ==
* Keep story IDs and node IDs stable.
* Keep complex action/trigger presets in shared helper methods.
* Use builder-based tests for large branching narratives.

